A PENSIONER who went missing in Glasgow has been found safe and well. Missing pensioner found safe and well in Glasgow A PENSIONER who went missing in Glasgow has been found safe and well.Patrick Scroggie, 78, who suffers from Alzheimer's, was last seen at 4.30pm yesterday.He left his home in Eastburn Road, in the Barmulloch area to go on a shopping trip.Police said he is known to frequent the Bishopbriggs and Springburn areas of Glasgow.He was found overnight. 